data(uint256).details: Returns the address of the data contract for the specified name.

doesNameExist(uint256).details: A name is considered to exist if its expiration timestamp is greater than zero.

params.nameID: The ID of the name to check.

returns._0: True if the name exists, false otherwise.

getExpirationTimestamp(uint256).details: Handles the following scenarios:      - For `HUMAN` names, returns the earlier of `paidTill` or `verifiedTill + grace period`.      - For `ARTIFICIAL` names, directly returns `paidTill`.      - For `SUBNAME` names, retrieves the expiration timestamp of the creator name recursively.      - Returns `0` for unknown or invalid name types.

params.nameID: The ID of the name to check.

returns._0: expirationTimestamp The expiration timestamp of the name, or `0` if invalid or expired.

params.potentialOwner: The address to check for ownership of a human name.

returns._0: True if the address owns a valid human name, false otherwise.

params.nameID: The ID of the human name to check.

returns._0: True if the human name is verified, false otherwise.

newArtificialName(string,uint256,bytes32.details: The function enforces the following:      - The provided name must be valid (without '#', '.' or similar characters).      - The creator name ID must correspond to a verified human name.      - The caller must own the creator name ID.      - The name must not already be registered.      - Sufficient payment must be provided to cover the cost of the name.

params.creatorNameID: The ID of the verified human name creating this artificial name.
params.duration_in_weeks: The duration in weeks for which the name is valid.
params.name: The base name to register (excluding the "##" suffix).
params.pubkeyX: The public key (X-coordinate) associated with the name.
params.pubkeyY: The public key (Y-coordinate) associated with the name.

returns._0: nameID The unique ID of the newly created artificial name.

newHumanName(string,bytes32,bytes32,uint.details: The function enforces the following:      - The provided name must be valid (without '#', '.' or similar characters).      - The name must not already be registered.      - The creator must not already own a human name.      - Sufficient payment must be provided to cover the cost of the name.

params.duration_in_weeks: The duration in weeks for which the name is valid.
params.name: The base name to register (excluding the "#" suffix).
params.pubkeyX: The public key (X-coordinate) associated with the name.
params.pubkeyY: The public key (Y-coordinate) associated with the name.

returns._0: nameID The unique ID of the newly created name.

newSubname(uint256,string).details: The function enforces the following:      - The provided name must be valid (without '#', '.' or similar characters).      - The parent name (nameID) must exist.      - The caller must own the parent name.      - If the parent name is of type HUMAN, it must be verified.

params.nameID: The ID of the parent name to which the subname will be linked.
params.subname: The subname to be created (excluding the parent name's suffix).

returns._0: subnameID The unique ID of the newly created subname.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setDataContract(uint256,address).details: Sets the data contract address for the specified name.

params.dataContract: The address of the data contract.

setNamePricingContract(address).details: Sets the name pricing contract address for Woolball.

params._namePricingContract: The address of the name pricing contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

getExpirationTimestamp(uint256).notice: Retrieves the expiration timestamp of a name based on its type.

hasHumanName(address).notice: Checks if the given address owns a valid human name.

isHumanNameVerified(uint256).notice: Checks if a human name is verified. A human name is verified if it has not expired (`paidTill > block.timestamp`) and is within the verification period (`verifiedTill > block.timestamp`).

newArtificialName(string,uint256,bytes32.notice: Creates a new artificial name with the suffix "##", e.g., "woolball##".

newHumanName(string,bytes32,bytes32,uint.notice: Creates a new human name with the suffix "#", e.g., "neiman#".

newSubname(uint256,string).notice: Creates a new subname associated with an existing name.          For example, given a name "neiman#", a subname "car.neiman#" can be created.
